__NOINDEX__
'''Siddha Yogi Sri Siva Shankar Baba''', or '''Baba''' as he is addressed,<ref name="samratchana">{{cite web|url=http://samratchana.net/about/baba/hisstory/en-us/default.asp|title=About Siddha Yogi Sri Siva Shankar Baba|publisher=Samratchana.net|accessdate=2010-02-06}}</ref> was born on January 28, 1949.<ref name="samratchana"/> During December of 1983, he performed kumbabishekam to the temple of Ayyappa that he had constructed in his home. On January 26, 1984, he (reportedly) underwent a death experience similar to that of Ramana MahaRishi, through a vision of [[Raghavendra Swami]].<ref name="samratchana"/> He has since then focussed on spirituality as his path in life. He has made many pilgrimages to numerous places of worship in India; featured articles of him chronicle his visits to Mount Kailash 11 times and Sabarimala 
70 times. <ref name="samratchana"/>
{{Rquote|Right|Never assume you can run away from anything. It is easier handling life by flowing along with it rather than trying to swim against the current and crashing on the rocks.|<ref name="samratchana"/>}}

==Institutions==
The institutions that Baba has pioneered, are involved in programs aimed at improving the quality of life of the needy and impoverished, and do not charge for the educational and medical services rendered.<ref name="samratchana"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://archives.chennaionline.com/toursntravel/placesofworship/shivasankar.asp|title=Ancient Shiva Temple at Tirusoolam|publisher=Archives.chennaionline.com|accessdate=January 25, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hinduonnet.com/mp/2003/02/06/stories/2003020600850300.htm |title=The Hindu: KELAMBAKKAM: For better living|publisher=Hinduonnet.com|date=February 6, 2003|accessdate=January 25, 2010}}</ref> The Sushil Hari International School (at [[Chennai, India]]), that Baba has founded,<ref name="samratchana"/> provides merit scholarship sponsoring the entire education and accommodation for industrious students.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.coachingindians.com/scholarships/total-care-scholarship.html|title=Total Care Scholarship,Read Detailed Information On Total Care Scholarship|publisher=Coachingindians.com|accessdate=January 25, 2010}}</ref> 

SushilHari International school focuses on methodologies that will foster a love for learning in students.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sushilharischool.org/sushilhari.aspx?id=6605|title=SushilHari International Residential School - Testimonials: From the Hostelites|publisher=Sushilharischool.org|accessdate=January 25, 2010}}</ref> Baba, as the founder of the School, records the following message for students,

{{Rquote|Right|When you are a student, your focus must be on studies. When you concentrate, you will definitely shine. Do not get distracted now. You will have time for other recreations of life later.|<ref>{{Cite Web|http://www.nilacharal.com/info/nilananbhan/sushilhari.html|title=Making Gods|publisher=Nilacharal.com|accessdate=2010-02-14}}</ref>}}

He discusses methods to handle daily life.<ref name='Voice of my Master'>{{cite book|last=Subramaniam|first=Karthik|authorlink=|coauthors=|title=Voice of my Master|publisher= |date=2001|location=Australia|pages=51}}</ref><ref name='Strange Story'>{{cite book|last=Handel|first=Richard & Marilyn|title=The Strange Story of Siva Shankar Baba|publisher=|date=2001|location=USA|pages=46|}}</ref><ref name='Nil!Kel!Vel!'>{{cite book|last=Raman|first=Dr.Prof.Gomathi|authorlink=|coauthors=|title=Nil!Kel!Vel![Halt!Listen!Win!]|publisher=|date=2002|location=India|pages=200}}</ref><ref name='God Son God Father'>{{cite book|last=N.C.Sangeethaa|coauthors = N.Geetha|title=God Son God Father|publisher=|date=2003|location=India|pages=120}}</ref><ref name='E-book by Nilacharal of ongoing interview series'>{{cite book|last=N.C.Sangeethaa|title=His Name is Siva Shankar|publisher=|date=2005|location=India & UK|url=http://www.nilacharal.com/news/religion/index.html}}</ref><ref name='HE Chose ME'>{{cite book|last=N.C.Sangeethaa|title=He Chose Me <U+2014> Maitreya in the Making|publisher|date=2009|location=India|pages=144}}</ref>

Siva Shankar Baba has established a secular commune with a Temple, Church, Mosque, Buddha Vihar, and Jain temple in the same place 'Sree Ramarajya'.<ref name="samratchana"/> 

===Institutions founded===

Baba has founded many schools and institutions. Samratchana is a center for [[self-realization]], typing, tailoring, foreign languages, music, dance, screen printing, among others; these courses are free of cost.<ref name="nila">{{cite web|url=http://www.nilacharal.com/info/nilananbhan/samratchana.html|title=A Silent Revolution|publisher=Nilacharal.com|accessdate=2010-02-14}}</ref> Sree Ramarajya is a [[secular commune]].<ref name="nila"/> SushilHari International School has gained international repute, and provides low-cost education.<ref name="nila"/> Grama Membattu Sangam is a rural upliftment center that provides free education and medical facilities to neighboring villagers.<ref name="nila"/>

